===Sources=== {{Refbegin|30em|indent=yes}} * {{cite book |last=Earhart |first=H. Byron |year=2004 |title=Japanese Religion: Unity and Diversity |edition=fourth |location=Belmont, CA |publisher=Wadsworth |isbn=978-0-534-17694-5 }} * {{cite book |last=Hardacre |first=Helen |title=Shinto: A History |location=Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2017 |isbn=978-0-19-062171-1 }} * {{cite journal |last = Nakajima |first = Michio |title = Shinto Deities that Crossed the Sea: Japan's "Overseas Shrines," 1868 to 1945 |year = 2010 |journal = Japanese Journal of Religious Studies |doi = 10.18874/jjrs.37.1.2010.21-46|doi-access = free }} * {{cite book |last=Picken |first=Stuart D. B. |author-link=Stuart D. B. Picken |title=Historical Dictionary of Shinto |edition=second |location=Lanham |publisher=Scarecrow Press |year=2011 |isbn=978-0-8108-7172-4 }} * {{cite journal |last=Suga |first=Kōji |title=A Concept of "Overseas Shinto Shrines": A Pantheistic Attempt by Ogasawara Shōzō and Its Limitations |journal=Japanese Journal of Religious Studies |volume=37 |issue=1 |year=2010 |pages=47–74 }} {{Refend}}
